快楽
かいらく【快楽】 ﾛｰﾏ(kairaku)
pleasure; enjoyment.
▲人生の快楽　the pleasures of life.
▲快楽にふける　be given [give oneself up] to pleasure; wallow [revel] in pleasure.
▲快楽を追う　seek [pursue, be intent on] pleasure; gather (life's) roses
・快楽を味わう　enjoy [taste, relish] pleasure
・いっさいの人生の快楽を捨てる　abandon all the pleasures of life; withdraw from all of life's comforts.
◧快楽原則　【精神分析】 the pleasure principle.
快楽殺人　【精神医】 lust murder; murder for pleasure.
快楽主義　〔快楽・幸福を最高善とする〕 hedonism; 〔エピクロス的快楽主義〕 Epicureanism.
▲快楽主義者　a hedonist; an epicurean.
